<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="390" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1735,2016]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1735,1761]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Distribution:</emphasis>
In the Amazonia of 
<collectingCountry box="[551,636,1735,1761]" name="Bolivia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[650,704,1736,1762]" name="Peru" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[718,789,1735,1761]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[803,916,1735,1761]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1048,1735,1761]" name="Venezuela" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1172,1735,1761]" name="Suriname" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1237,1324,1735,1761]" name="Guyana" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral 2017). In 
<collectingCountry box="[456,566,1771,1797]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
there are records from 
<collectingRegion box="[829,934,1771,1797]" country="Colombia" name="Guaviare" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Guaviare</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[945,1037,1771,1797]" country="Colombia" name="Caqueta" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Caquetá</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1091,1172,1771,1797]" country="Colombia" name="Vaupes" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Vaupés</collectingRegion>
departments (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1422,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1735,2016]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1807,1833]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[393,675,1807,1833]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis box="[393,675,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Loxopholis percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from other sympatric and similar species of the genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,261,1843,1869]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
in having an upper dark stripe on the flanks 1–3 scales wide (flanks completely covered by a wide dark band in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[242,379,1879,1905]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis box="[242,379,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[434,598,1879,1905]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[434,598,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); sharply keeled ventral scales (smooth or weakly keeled in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1279,1429,1880,1905]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">
<emphasis box="[1279,1429,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. caparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, smooth in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[273,410,1915,1941]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis box="[273,410,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); fourth pair of chin-shield reduced (not reduced in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[1009,1147,1915,1941]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1147,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[1205,1370,1915,1941]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[1205,1370,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and second and third supraocular subequal and larger than the others (third supraocular larger than the second in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). For a more detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[708,921,1987,2016]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="391" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,249]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Remarks:</emphasis>
In this work, we extend the known distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[901,1084,151,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis box="[901,1084,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1123,1233,151,177]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Colombia</collectingCountry>
to the municipality of Acacias, 
<collectingRegion box="[320,514,187,213]" country="Colombia" name="Meta" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Meta department</collectingRegion>
, ca. 
<quantity box="[564,649,186,213]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" unit="km" value="175.0">175 km</quantity>
NW from its most northern previous record in San José del 
<collectingRegion box="[1327,1432,187,213]" country="Colombia" name="Guaviare" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Guaviare</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,257,223,249]" country="Colombia" name="Guaviare" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Guaviare</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
